line_1: To Surry's wood-crown'd hills my steps allur'd:
line_2: Where on Thamesis' banks I liv'd immur'd,
When thowes dissolve the snawy hoord,
An' float the jinglan icy boord,

line_1: With easy charms the Jebusites allur'd
line_2: Her artless looks, nor tim'rous, nor assur'd,

line_1: His brainless Off-Spring by their Vice allur'd,
line_2: Destroy the Crop, which he with care manur'd;
" My days in these still bowers immur'd,

line_1: And by their plaintive strains perchance allur'd,
line_2: Two turtle doves the pensive fair secur'd.
